    "body": "The prompt is shown once per computer. You can read what we track in our [privacy policy](https://hardhat.org/privacy-policy.html), but it's not a lot of data. We try to be as minimal with tracking as possible, respecting our users' privacy.\r\n\r\nIf you want to reset it you can run `npx hardhat --verbose`, and you'll see a log like this\r\n\r\n```\r\n  hardhat:core:global-dir Looking up Client Id at /Users/pato/Library/Application Support/hardhat-nodejs/analytics.json +0ms\r\n``` \r\n\r\nThen, delete that file.",
